Backlog section: Candidate 5 — BulkOperationFactory.

## Context

First PR in Candidate 5. The current `bulk-ops-queue.service.ts` is a 36-line BullMQ wrapper. The real orchestration (idempotency-key parsing + bulk_operations existence check + insert + enqueue) lives in each route that needs bulk ops — currently `routes/bulk-import.ts` and the bulk-ops branch of `routes/queues.ts`. Future endpoints (e.g., bulk delete posts) would copy the same dance.

See [BACKLOG.md](../blob/main/BACKLOG.md) → Architectural Deepening → Candidate 5.

## Scope

- Add `packages/api/src/services/bulk-operation.factory.ts` (or a similar location) exporting:
  ```ts
  interface BulkOperationFactory {
    startBulkOperation(args: {
      userId: string;
      idempotencyKey: string | undefined;
      type: 'import_scheduled' | 'import_queue' | 'queue_bulk_op_X' | ...;
      params: Record<string, unknown>;  // job payload
      jobName: JobName;
    }): Promise<{
      bulkOperationId: string;
      jobId: string | null;
      replay: boolean;
    }>;
  }
  ```
- Move the full chain into the factory:
  - Parse + validate `Idempotency-Key` header (UUID validation)
  - Lookup existing `bulk_operations` row by (userId, idempotencyKey)
  - If exists: return `{ bulkOperationId, jobId: null, replay: true }`
  - Otherwise: insert new `bulk_operations` row, enqueue job, return `{ bulkOperationId, jobId, replay: false }`
- Inject `BulkOpsQueueService` + `Db` via the factory constructor
- Unit tests covering: new operation path, replay path, invalid idempotency key, transaction rollback if insert + enqueue is non-atomic (verify the ordering matches existing semantics)
- Keep the existing `bulk-ops-queue.service.ts` for now — R5.2 / R5.3 switch consumers, then R5.3 sweep removes the standalone service if subsumed

## Out of scope

- Switching consumers (R5.2, R5.3)
- Removing the existing `bulk-ops-queue.service.ts` (R5.3 sweep)
- Moving the factory into `@sms/shared` — keep in api package since both consumers are routes; cross-package isn't needed

## Acceptance

- `pnpm --filter @sms/api build` and test pass
- Factory unit tests achieve full branch coverage
- No existing callers changed

